    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="48"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.927233</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Far Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Hamilton</hi>)<note n="65a" xml:id="d48fn1"
                        >Addressed to the Secretary of State and the Under Secretary of
                        State.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-31">January 31,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>We believe it advisable that this Government in some way make known to the
                    Japanese Government its interest in Japan’s mediation of the Thai-French
                    Indochinese controversy. The procedure suggested in one of the attached
                        telegrams<note n="66" xml:id="d48fn2">See telegram No. 76, February 3, 8
                        p.m., to the Ambassador in Japan, <ref target="#pg_54">p. 54</ref>.</note>
                    is designed to do that in a way which would not expose this Government to the
                    same risk of a rebuff as the procedures previously discussed.<note n="67"
                        xml:id="d48fn3">Notation by the Secretary of State: “Only a suggestion to
                        consider: Grew might accompany this cable by copy of my statement of
                        principles of July 1937, so Japan cannot claim not to understand U. S. exact
                        attitude. C. H.” For the Secretary’s statement of July 16, 1937, see <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_325">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 325</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M[<hi rend="smallcaps">axwell</hi>] M. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >amilton</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
